value.title: Historic border numbers undercut Biden claim that surge 'happens every year'
value.excerpt: President Biden last month downplayed the surge in migrants coming to the southern border, saying surges happen "every year" -- but while that is the case, the numbers released Thursday show that the current surge is dwarfing anything in recent memory.

value.title: Biden on the Second Amendment: 'No amendment is absolute'
value.excerpt: President Biden on Thursday, in rolling out a set of executive orders on gun control, said "no amendment is absolute," while maintaining that "nothing" he is recommending "impinges" on the Second Amendment.

value.title: Biden's $100B internet overhaul will hurt consumers, stifle innovation: Former FCC chairman
value.excerpt: Former FCC Chairman Ajit Pai said Thursday that the allocation of $100 billion to expand broadband networks in the U.S. under the Biden administration will only serve to hurt consumers and stifle innovation.

value.excerpt: Two House Republicans are demanding that the Environmental Protection Agency provide records related to a decision by the agency’s new leader to remove dozens of scientists and other experts from two key advisory boards.

value.title: Parents of 445 migrant children separated at border under Trump still have not been found, court filing says
value.excerpt: The parents of 445 migrant children separated from their families due to Trump administration policies at the US-Mexico border between 2017 and 2018 have still not been located, down from 506, according to a Wednesday court filing.

value.title: Rep. McCaul says Biden's immigration policies a 'victory' for traffickers and 'very bad defeat' for children
value.excerpt: Rep. Michael McCaul, R-Texas, slammed President Biden's border policies Wednesday on "The Story," calling them a "victory" for traffickers, who separate children from their parents and bring them on a "very dangerous journey" to the United States.
